the energy density and power density of the flywheel, and the parameters of both first stage and the second stage flywheel were selected reasonably, which provided a theoretical basis and design method for designing and analyzing of the multistage flywheel energy storage device. ## **2. Flywheel energy storage characteristics** As a rotating mechanical element, the physics of the flywheel is simple. The flywheel gains momentum after applying torque and begins to rotate, and the rotor continues to rotate after the initial torque is removed. After overcoming the friction force and air resistance of the bearing, the remaining kinetic energy drives the",
